    "severity": "critical",
    "description": "The matchHeaders function has inverted logic. When a configured header matches the request headers, the function returns false (indicating no match), but it should return true (indicating a match). This causes fault injection to be skipped for requests that should be affected. The function is used by fault_filter.cc line 130 which skips fault injection when matchHeaders returns false. With the inverted logic, requests that match the configured filter headers are incorrectly excluded from fault injection.",
