code_changes.new_string:
  {
    "file": "source/common/http/header_utility.cc",
    "line": 38,
    "severity": "critical",
    "description": "The matchHeaders function has inverted logic for matching headers. When a configured header matches the request headers, the function returns false (indicating no match), but it should return true (indicating a match). This causes fault injection to be skipped for requests that should be affected. The function is used by fault_filter.cc line 130 which skips fault injection when matchHeaders returns false. With the inverted logic, requests that match the configured filter headers are incorrectly excluded from fault injection. The fix requires restructuring the logic to return true when any configured header matches, and false when none match.",
    "fix_patch": "--- a/source/common/http/header_utility.cc
+++ b/source/common/http/header_utility.cc
@@ -38,14 +38,18 @@
 bool HeaderUtility::matchHeaders(const HeaderMap& request_headers,
                                  const std::vector<HeaderDataPtr>& config_headers) {
   // No headers to match is considered a match.
   if (!config_headers.empty()) {
     for (const HeaderDataPtr& cfg_header_data : config_headers) {
       if (cfg_header_data->matchesHeaders(request_headers)) {
-        return false;
+        return true;
       }
     }
+    return false;
   }
-
   return true;
 }
"
  },

